parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spark plug failure can cause the engine to misfire, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident. In some cases, the spark plug can blow out of the cylinder head, causing damage to the engine and potentially leading to a fire.
symptoms: Spark plug blows out of cylinder head

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intake manifold failure can cause coolant leaks, engine overheating, and potentially lead to engine failure.
Engine stalling can cause a loss of control, potentially leading to an accident.
Exhaust manifold failure can cause exhaust fumes to enter the vehicle, potentially leading to carbon monoxide poisoning.
Transmission failure can cause a loss of power, potentially leading to an accident.
The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants may not be adequately protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities to the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries or distractions to the driver, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without a crash or impact
causing unnecessary distractions or injuries to the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning airbag sensor can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in a crash or unintended deployment, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: causing airbags to fail to deploy or deploy unnecessarily

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint of the occupant in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract properly
the seat belt gets tangled or twisted
the seat belt does not release or latch properly
the seat belt makes a metallic clinking noise when in use.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gas Fume Odor Inside the Vehicle
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of a gas fume odor inside the vehicle can cause discomfort, nausea, and potentially lead to health problems for the occupants.
symptoms: A strong gas fume odor is present inside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The emergency brake does not engage properly
the vehicle rolls or moves when the emergency brake is engaged.
